npm run dev: to run REACT
python app.py: to run Flask
npm install react-router-dom: This installs a router for React, so app can have mutile URLs without needing to reloaded


To run API: 
cd into api, 
pip install -r requirements.txt
source .venv/bin/activate
python app.py

To run UI on everything: 
npm i -D vite-plugin-svgr //download svgr images

VITE_API_BASE_URL=http://192.168.0.80:5001 npm run build

To open Xcode and build app on Iphone:
npx cap copy ios                                        
npx cap open ios     

SQL Basics - Your Database Language

  SQL = Structured Query Language - It's how we talk to databases.

  Think of your database like a spreadsheet:

  users table:
  +----+----------+---------------+---------------+
  | id | username | password_salt | password_hash |
  +----+----------+---------------+---------------+
  | 1  | testuser | abc123...     | def456...     |
  | 2  | alice    | xyz789...     | uvw012...     |
  +----+----------+---------------+---------------+

  üîç The 4 Basic SQL Operations:

  1. SELECT - Read data (like "find")

  -- Get ALL columns from ALL users
  SELECT * FROM users;

  -- Get SPECIFIC columns from ALL users  
  SELECT id, username FROM users;

  -- Get data WHERE condition matches
  SELECT * FROM users WHERE username = 'alice';

  2. INSERT - Add new data

  -- Add a new user
  INSERT INTO users (username, password_salt, password_hash)
  VALUES ('john', 'salt123', 'hash456');

  3. UPDATE - Change existing data

  -- Change Alice's username
  UPDATE users SET username = 'alice_new' WHERE id = 2;

  4. DELETE - Remove data

  -- Remove user with id 1
  DELETE FROM users WHERE id = 1;